column2: ERROR 43 Y CURRENT
• The slider is stopped with an obstacle. • Overcurrent error has arisen on the Y-axis motor
1) Remove the obstacle. 2) Turn on the power. 3) Replace Y axis motor. 4) Replace a main PCB.
ERROR 44 SCAN RANGE
• Out-of-range scan was attempted.
1) Report the problem to Development Division. Upgrade the firmware later.
ERROR 50 MEDIA SENSE
• The edge of the media has not been detected.
1) Check if the paper is off the rubber part of the platen. 2)In the case of failure of paper detection sensor, replace the sensor. (# Confirm with test paper sensor)
ERROR 51 Y ORIGIN
• Y-axis origin detection has not been successfully carried out.
1) Replace a Y axis motor. 2) Replace a Y origin sensor. 3) Replace a IO PCB. 4) Replace a main PCB.
ERROR 53 STEP ORIGIN
• Capping or wiping origin detection failed.
1) Check and correct the capping or wiping mechanism. 2) Replace the capping or wiping origin sensor.
ERROR 60 FLASHING nnnn
Flashing timeout. n=UHC No.1~8
1) Replace the slider board. 2) Replace the head FPC cable.
ERROR 61 TEMP ss nnnnnnnn
Head control temperature trouble. n=UHC No.1~8
1) Ink level is too low. Ambient temperature is too high (remove the cause). 2) Replace the slider board. 3) Replace the head FPC cable.
ERROR 70 WATER LACK
• Hot water tank level is too low.
1) Add water.
ERROR 71 WATER DEVICE ss
• ss=01: Hot water tank temperature control problem. • ss=02: Hot water tank line problem. • ss=03: Head temperature problem.
1) Replace the water heater. 2) Correct the hot water line. 3) Replace the head.
ERROR 72 UV POWER OFF (Copper-iron and Inverter type power supply unit )
The breaker of UV device is off. • The UV interface cable is not connected to the device.
• The breaker of UV device is off. 1) Turn on the breaker of UV device. • The UV interface cable is not connected to the device. 1) The UV interface cable connects to the device.
ERROR 72 UV POWER OFF (Inverter type power supply unit )
• The radiator fan of UV irradiation device is defective. • The UV lamp control cable is broken.
1) Replace the UV irradiation device. 1) Replace the UV lamp control cable.
ERROR 73 UV DEVICE 01 ERROR 73 UV DEVICE 02
• 01: The shutter is not opened. • 02: The shutter is not closed. • The shutter switch for open/ close is defective.  • UV lamp control cable has broken of the wire.
1) Replace the UV irradiation device with a new one.  1) Replace the UV lamp control cable with a new one.
ERROR 73 UV DEVICE 01 ERROR 73 UV DEVICE 02 ERROR 73 UV DEVICE 04 (Shutter)
• 01: The shutter is not opened. • 02: The shutter is not closed. • The shutter switch for open/ close is defective. • UV lamp control cable has broken of the wire.
1) Replace the UV irradiation device with a new one.
ERROR 73 UV DEVICE 03 (Lamp.V20)
• The UV lamp is tried to relight with burning. • UV lamp cable has not connected to the terminal block. • UV lamp have not been set. • UV lamp cable has broken down or the connector is defective.

1) Turn the lamp on after cooling down the UV lamp. 1) Make sure that the UV lamp cable have connected to the terminal block in the UV irradiation device. 2) Make sure to set the UV lamp 1) Replace the UV lamp cable with a new one.
ERROR 73 UV DEVICE 03 (Lamp.Volt)
• Voltage is abnormal conditions by the UV lamp anomaly. • Voltage increase or decrease.
1) Replace the UV lamp with a new one.
ERROR 74 UV DEVICE

• The UV lamp is tried to relight with burning. • UV lamp cable has not connected to the terminal block. • UV lamp have not been set. • UV lamp cable has broken down or the connector is defective. • Voltage is abnormal conditions by the UV lamp anomaly. • Voltage increase or decrease. • UV power supply internal parts are abnormal heating.

1) Turn the lamp on after cooling down the UV lamp. 1) Make sure that the UV lamp cable have connected to the terminal block in the UV irradiation device. 2) Make sure to set the UV lamp 1) Replace the UV lamp cable with a new one. 1) Replace the UV lamp with a new one. 1) Replace the UV power supply unit with a new one.
ERROR 74 UV DEVICE (TEMP lamp is lighting)
• Malfunction of UV irradiation device cooling fan. • UV lamp control cable has broken of the wire.
1) Replace the UV irradiation device with a new one. 1) Replace the UV lamp control cable with a new one
ERROR 74 UV DEVICE (ERROR)
• UV power supply internal parts are abnormal heating.

1) Make sure that the air filters in the front or the rear side is not covered with objects. 2) Make sure that the rear side fan of the UV power supply is running. 3) Replace the UV power supply unit with a new one.
ERROR 90 F/W ss
• Firmware problem.
1) Report the problem to Development Division. Upgrade the firmware later.
! UV LAMP UV LAMP CHANGE :ent
• Changing time for the UV lamp.
1) Replace the UV lamp with new one.
! UV LAMP UV LEVEL CHK :ent
• The UV lamp level has exceeded the predetermined amounts of time.
1) Confirm the UV lamp light level.
<<LOC.>>NEAR END COLOR :KCMYcmW
• The amount of ink remaining in the ink cartridge is insufficient.
1) Printing can be continued in file-by-file basis by pressing the [REMOTE] key.
! INK END COLOR :KCMYcmW
• There is no ink in ink cartridge.
1) Replace the ink cartridge of which color is shown on the LCD with a new one.
! INK CARTRIDGE COLOR :KCMYcmW
• The ink cartridge is not installed to the ink station.
1) Install the ink cartridge(s) corresponding with the color shown on the display.
! CARTRIDGE CHECK COLOR :KCMYcmW
• Not operated as a menu.
1) Confirm the ink cartridge.
! INK TANK WASTE TANK FULL
• Waste ink tank is full.
1) Remove the waste ink tank and set an empty waste ink tank.
! COVER OPEN CLOSE A COVER
• The cover is open.
1) Close the cover.
(COVER OPEN) PRESS <ENT> KEY
• [ENTER] key check after closing the cover.
1) Press the [ENTER] key and restart the device.
! WRONG INK IC COLOR :KCMYcmW
• IC chip on the ink cartridge has not been read properly.
1) Re-insert the displayed inkcartridge. 2) Replace the ink-cartridge.
<<LOC.>>useLIMIT COLOR :KCMYcmW
• The use-by date of the inkcartridge has expired.
1) Replace ink-cartridge ahead of time. (Possible to print)
!Expiration: 2MON COLOR :KCMYcmW
• 2 months passed after the useby date of the ink-cartridge.
1) Replace ink-cartridge
NON-ORIGINAL INK COLOR :KCMYcmW
• The cartridge is not Mimaki`s genuine ink-cartridge.
1) Use Mimaki`s genuine inkcartridge.
!CAP SENSOR FAIL
• If the cam rotates half from the bottom position of the capping, capping sensor cannot be detected.
1) Capping sensor may have an error. 2) Sensor position or adjustment of the lowest point position may be inadequate.
!ORIGIN SETTING IS OUT OF RANGE
• The origin has been set outside the printing area.
1) Set the origin inside the printing area.
